description:
&lt;p&gt;An exciting opportunity has arisen to join our dynamic Resourcing and HR Operations team.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are looking for an experienced and knowledgeable professional to join our team as a HR officer. This post will support the Resourcing &amp; HR Operations team in delivering appropriate operational support for Trust’s Divisions. You will be responsible for all HR administrative work associated with amendment to terms and conditions for staff, advising staff on policies, dealing with termination and working closely with payroll providers.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The successful post holder will have be proficient in the use of TRAC, NHS Jobs, And ESR; and advising managers on policy and procedure. Knowledge of NHS Employers regulations is highly desirable as is the ability to organise and prioritise comprehensive workload and the flexibility to adapt to changing priorities.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Working with C&amp;I can open up many possibilities and we are able to support you in career journey offering you training and educational opportunities, and also support your career development.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details, please contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Umme Farha&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Resourcing and HR Operations Team Leader&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Umme.farha@candi.nhs.uk&lt;/p&gt;
